-- Stocks Rise, Led by Zodiac Aerospace; SEB, Orco Climb, Theolia Declines
-- David Altaner
-- 2010-07-12T11:12:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/alstom-camaieu-neopost-riber-theolia-french-equity-preview.html

          
          
             France’s benchmark CAC 40 Index rose
2.82, or 0.1 percent, to 3,557.3 at 1:10 p.m. in Paris. The SBF-
120 Index also advanced 0.1 percent.  
 The following companies’ shares were among the most active
in France today. Symbols are in parentheses.  
 Groupe SEB SA  (SK FP) rallied 6.9 percent to 58.81 euros, a
seventh straight gain. The world’s largest maker of countertop
kitchen appliances was upgraded to “buy” from “neutral” at
Goldman Sachs Group Inc.  
 Orco Property Group SA  (ORC FP) rose 5.2 percent to 5.10
euros. The developer overhauling operations under a court-
approved plan said it recovered 11.9 million euros ($15 million)
in cash.  
 Theolia SA  (TEO FP) fell 4.7 percent to 1.23 euros. The
Aix-en-Provence-based wind-power company may add to its presence
in Morocco following its capital-raising campaign, Journal des
Finances said July 10, citing an interview with Chief Executive
Officer  Fady Khallouf .  
 Zodiac Aerospace SA  (ZC FP) climbed 4.8 percent to 41.69
euros. Europe’s biggest maker of airplane seats rejected a
takeover approach from jet-engine-maker Safran SA, saying the
companies have little overlap or potential cost savings.  
